                  <additions>
                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a5_568">
                           <locus target="#190v">-190v</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">مالك هذا الكتاب حسين بن صديق ابن احمد وكاتبه احمد ابن عمر  غفر الله عنه كتب في بلد دامتي امين</q>
                           <desc>Colophon</desc>
                           <note>The whole note is written by the scribe.</note>
                           <note>: <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC0114IHA">Dāmōt</placeName>
                              <p>
                                 Mentioned
                              : <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0556IHA">حسين بن صديق بن احمد </persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                 Mentioned
                              : <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0556IHA">حسين بن صديق بن احمد </persName>
                              </p>
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3_568">
                           <locus target="#149v-162r-175r">-149v, 162r, 175r</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Ǧuz’ markers: al-ǧuz’ with number in letters</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note>The text is written in red. The numbers given are 28, 29 and 30.</note>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2_568">
                           <locus target="#12v-24r-36v-49r-60v-72v-85r-98r-110v-123r-136v">-12v, 24r, 36v, 49r, 60v, 72v, 85r, 98r, 110v, 123r, 136v</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Ǧuz’ markers: large decorated circles</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note>The circles are drawn in red ink: double circle with a dot in the center. The decorations are made in red and black ink. The circle on fol. 36v is undecorated.</note>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a1_568">
                           <locus target="#2v">-2v</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Large circle in the margins</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note>The circle is placed in the beginning of sūra 19. It resembles the circles that are used as ǧuz’ markers on other folios.</note>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a0_568">
                           <locus target="#Throughout">-Throughout</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Ṯumn markers.</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                     </t:list>
                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1r">-1r</locus>
                           <desc>Ownership</desc>
                           <q>هذ الكتا ملك حسن بن علي بن صديق \ هذ الكتاب ملك حسن بن علي بن حسين بن صديق بن احمد وبلده قالُّو وقريته بوء</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
